coding.display: To contact a local service within 6 hours

text.div: To contact a local service within 6 hours (Dx06) <br/> <br/> Selected service: Urgent Treatment Centre (GP led), Royal South Hant<br/>
Illness<br/>Warm to touch<br/>Nausea without vomiting<br/>Abdominal pain also present<br/>Moderately severe pain<br/>Flank pain<br/>Fever at time of assessment or in last 12 hours<br/>

An injury or health problem was the reason for the contact.<br/>Heavy bleeding had not occurred in the previous 30 minutes.<br/>An illness or health problem was the main problem.<br/>User Comments: Pharmacy ITK Testing<br/>The individual was not fighting for breath.<br/>The main reason for the contact was not an allergic reaction, chest/upper back pain, recent fit/seizure, suicide attempt, new confusion or suspected stroke.<br/>The main reason for contact was not declared diabetic hypo/hyperglycaemia or ICD shock.<br/>The skin on the torso felt normal, warm or hot.<br/>Pathway selected - Vomiting and/or Nausea<br/>The individual had not vomited.<br/>The individual did not also have diarrhoea.<br/>The symptoms did not follow drinking alcohol.<br/>Abdominal pain was also present.<br/>The pain interfered with normal activity.<br/>The individual was able to carry out most or all normal activities.<br/>The individual had not ingested a harmful or toxic substance.<br/>There had been no black and tarry or red/maroon bowel motions.<br/>There was no new or worsening confusion.<br/>Breathing harder or faster when doing nothing was not described.<br/>There was no new shoulder tip pain or pain in the lower right abdomen.<br/>The individual had not been in constant pain for 4 hours or more.<br/>There was no previous history of diabetes.<br/>There was flank pain.<br/>There was a fever at the time of assessment or within the previous 12 hours.<br/>There was no new, widespread, red rash.<br/>Instructions given were: The individual needs to contact a local service within 6 hours.<br/>Directory of Services referral: Urgent Treatment Centre (GP led), Royal South Hants Hospital<br/>

I will arrange for a clinician to contact the individual. I need to ask some further questions in order to determine the best way to do this.<br/>If there are any new symptoms, or if the condition gets worse, changes or you have any other concerns, call us back.<br/> <br/>
<content>To contact a local service within 6 hours<br/> </content> <br/> <br/>
